        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "I (agent) interpret the use of projection television at the 1970s computer fair as a pioneering marketing tactic. While most competitors likely relied on static displays or text-heavy demos, Apple's focus on visual spectacle ('stole the show') highlighted the consumer-friendly, multimedia potential of the personal computer, differentiating it from purely technical hobbyist machines.",
