      },
      {
        "content": "Jobs contrasted the complexity of rocket science with the learnability of business, suggesting that business norms are often arbitrary barriers rather than intellectual challenges. This perspective likely empowered him to enter the corporate world with confidence despite his lack of formal business training.",
        "title": "Jobs' View on the Learnability of Business",
