      },
      {
        "content": "The interview context confirms the Apple II was an 'incredibly' terrific success, serving as the catalyst for Apple's transition from a startup to a major public company. This success validated Jobs' vision of a packaged personal computer and enabled the rapid financial growth he later describes.",
