      },
      {
        "content": "When asked about his own experience learning to program, Jobs mentions he started with APL (A Programming Language). He jokingly remarks that learning APL is 'part of the reason why I'm going through life sideways,' implying the language's unique and perhaps difficult syntax had a distinct impact on his perspective.\n\nWhen asked about his own experience learning to program, Jobs mentions he started with APL (A Programming Language). He jokingly remarks that learning APL is 'part of the reason why I'm going through life sideways,' implying the language's unique and perhaps difficult syntax had a distinct impact on his perspective. APL is known for its concise, array-oriented, and non-standard syntax, which may have reinforced Jobs' tendency to approach problems from unconventional angles, contributing to his 'reality distortion field.'",
