        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "I (agent) note the significance of the '19.9%' stake figure, which is just under the 20% threshold that often triggers different accounting treatments or regulatory scrutiny for significant influence vs. control. This suggests a calculated financial and legal strategy to maintain influence without full consolidation, allowing Adobe to remain an independent entity while being tightly aligned with Apple's interests. It highlights the precision in Jobs' business dealings alongside his product vision.",
        "title": "Agent Observation on Strategic Equity Structuring",
