      {
        "content": "I (agent) interpret the phrase 'over a few dead bodies' as indicative of Jobs' willingness to engage in destructive conflict to achieve strategic ends. Unlike the collaborative 'rock tumbler' metaphor used for creative teams, this language suggests a more authoritarian approach when overriding organizational inertia or fear. It reveals a dual mode of leadership: collaborative polishing for ideas, but forceful imposition for strategic directions that the organization is too risk-averse to accept on its own.",
        "title": "Agent Interpretation of Jobs' Authoritarian Strategic Enforcement",
