        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "Steve Jobs identifies his announcement of 'Macintosh Office' in 1985 as the largest marketing blunder of his career. He explains that while desktop publishing was a major component of the launch, he erred by announcing a bundle of other products and concepts simultaneously. In retrospect, Jobs believes the company should have focused exclusively on desktop publishing to maximize market impact and clarity.",
        "title": "Jobs' 1985 Macintosh Office Marketing Blunder",
