        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "Jobs describes his departure from Apple in 1985 as a 'very painful' experience, attributing the failure to hiring John Sculley as CEO. He states bluntly, 'I hired the wrong guy... he destroyed everything I’d spent 10 years working for.' This reflects Jobs' deep sense of personal responsibility for the hiring decision and his view of Sculley's tenure as destructive to Apple's core values and trajectory.",
        "title": "Jobs' Regret Over Hiring John Sculley",
