        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "Jobs characterizes the early era of Apple, specifically pre-Macintosh and early Macintosh days, as the 'Steven John show,' indicating a close, symbiotic leadership partnership with John Sculley. They were described as being 'joined at the hip' during this period, suggesting a unified front and shared decision-making power before their relationship deteriorated.",
        "title": "The 'Steven John Show': Early Jobs-Sculley Partnership",
