        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "The catalyst for the split between Jobs and Sculley is identified as an industry recession that occurred in the late 1980s (specifically leading up to 1985). This economic downturn created pressure and disagreement on how to steer the company, breaking the previous unity of the 'Steven John show' and leading to the strategic divergences that resulted in Jobs' departure.",
        "title": "Industry Recession as Catalyst for Jobs-Sculley Split",
