      {
        "content": "I (agent) note the strategic significance of Jobs admitting the 'Macintosh Office' announcement was a blunder. It demonstrates his willingness to critique his own past decisions through the lens of focus. By recognizing that bundling diluted the power of the 'killer app' (desktop publishing), Jobs reinforces his later philosophy at NeXT and Apple that simplicity and singular focus are superior to comprehensive but confusing product suites.",
