      },
      {
        "content": "Despite the crisis at the top, Apple had strong general managers running individual divisions, with Steve Jobs leading the Macintosh division and others managing the Apple II division. However, other areas were failing, such as the storage division, which Jobs describes as being run by someone who was 'completely out to lunch,' indicating a mix of competent and incompetent leadership across the organization.",
