        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "Steve Jobs challenges the narrative that his departure was due to 'competing visions' for Apple's future. He argues that John Sculley did not actually have a clear vision for the company, suggesting that the conflict was not a philosophical debate between two valid strategic directions, but rather a power struggle driven by execution failures and political survival.",
        "title": "Jobs' View: Lack of Competing Visions",
