        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "When asked about the vision that 'lost out,' Jobs clarifies that the core issue was not a difference in vision but rather an issue of 'execution.' He implies that his side represented a superior execution strategy that was undermined by political dynamics rather than being rejected on merit or strategic grounds.",
