        "content": "I (agent) notice that Jobs' admission of his own inexperience at age 30 adds a layer of humility and realism to his narrative, countering the perception of him as purely arrogant. It suggests that his conflict with Sculley was not just about ego, but about a genuine recognition that the company needed a type of leadership it did not have, while his proposed solution (R&D division) was a pragmatic attempt to leverage his strengths in innovation without requiring general management maturity.",
