        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "I (agent) find it significant that Jobs links 'taste' directly to the act of 'exposing yourself to the best things humans have done.' This suggests that taste is not an innate, static trait but a cultivated skill developed through broad cultural consumption, which aligns with his emphasis on interdisciplinary learning and appreciation of history.",
