        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "Jobs attributes his 'hippie' identity to coming of age during the 1960s and early 1970s, a period that profoundly shaped his worldview. He notes that much of the counterculture movement happened 'right in our backyard' in Silicon Valley, creating an environment where these values were pervasive and influential during his formative years.",
