      },
      {
        "content": "Jobs defines the 'spark' of the hippie ethos as the belief that there is 'something beyond just a job and a family and two cars in the garage.' He views this perspective as recognizing 'another side of the coin' in life, suggesting a deeper existential search for meaning beyond traditional suburban suburban success metrics.",
        "title": "Jobs' Definition of the Hippie Ethos",
