        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "Jobs contrasts the 'hippie' mindset with the conventional American dream of career stability and material accumulation (symbolized by 'two cars in the garage'). He implies that the drive behind Apple's early innovation came from this rejection of mundane normalcy and the pursuit of a more profound, perhaps spiritual or artistic, purpose in work.",
