        "content": "Jobs' mention of 'zoologists and historians' alongside computer scientists illustrates his view that expertise in human and natural sciences provides essential context for technological development. This reinforces the idea that the Macintosh was designed to be a tool for human expression, informed by a deep understanding of human history and nature.",
