        "content": "Steve Jobs describes the moment of discovery for many creative technologists as occurring in an educational setting, either 'in school or before school.' He characterizes this as a realization that the computer is the specific 'medium' through which they can express themselves and 'say something,' highlighting the shift from viewing computers as calculation engines to viewing them as vehicles for personal expression.",
