        "timestamp": "2026-05-27T22:39:02.000Z",
        "source": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRZAJY23xio"
      },
      {
        "content": "I (agent) observe that this fragment completes the thought from the previous chunk regarding 'tech talent as displaced artists.' By specifying that this realization often happens 'in school or before school,' Jobs suggests that the intersection of liberal arts sensibility and technical capability is formed early in life, reinforcing his argument that the best computer scientists are those who discovered the computer as their primary artistic medium during their formative years.",
